<p>If you would like to receive these text messages from Student Records and Registration Office text the word<strong> DEADLINES</strong> to <strong>46786</strong>.</p>
<p><img height="251" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Student Record and Registration/Standards/phones.png" width="710" /></p>
<p>Note: Spring Semester 2011 BYU-Idaho experimented with sending a text message to all students on campus concerning the full semester course drop deadline.&nbsp; This caused a 150% increase in dropped courses that day compared to previous semesters.&nbsp; It also contributed to a significant decrease in petition requests by students to remove W grades from their transcript.</p>
<p><strong>Are there fees or charges with these text messages?</strong> There  are no additional charges beyond the standard rates that you pay to  your carrier for sending and receiving text messages. Most people that do a lot of  texting have unlimited plans for sending and receiving text messages to  their mobile phones. You should contact your mobile phone carrier if you  have questions. &nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>How do I remove myself from this texting list after I have opted in?</strong> Text STOP, END, QUIT, CANCEL or REMOVE to the shared short code and you are automatically removed from the list.</p>
